Print Methods

Source: R/print-methods.R
printsoa.Rd

Print Methods

# S3 method for SOA
print(x, ...)

# S3 method for MDLE
print(x, ...)

# S3 method for Spattern
print(x, ...)

# S3 method for dim_wt_tab
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

object to be printed (SOA, OSOA, MDLE, Spattern)

...

further arguments for function print

Value

no value is returned

Examples

myOSOA <- OSOAs_regular(s=3, k=3, optimize=FALSE)
myOSOA
#>       [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
#>  [1,]    0    2    0    2
#>  [2,]   13   13    1   14
#>  [3,]   26   24    2   26
#>  [4,]   25   12   12    1
#>  [5,]    2   26   13   13
#>  [6,]   12    1   14   25
#>  [7,]   14   25   24    0
#>  [8,]   24    0   25   12
#>  [9,]    1   14   26   24
#> [10,]   10   10   10   10
#> [11,]   23   21   11   22
#> [12,]    6    8    9    7
#> [13,]    8   23   22    9
#> [14,]    9    7   23   21
#> [15,]   22    9   21    6
#> [16,]   21    6    7   11
#> [17,]    7   11    8   23
#> [18,]   11   22    6    8
#> [19,]   20   18   20   18
#> [20,]    3    5   18    3
#> [21,]   16   16   19   15
#> [22,]   15    4    5   20
#> [23,]   19   15    3    5
#> [24,]    5   20    4   17
#> [25,]    4   17   17   19
#> [26,]   17   19   15    4
#> [27,]   18    3   16   16
#> OSOA, strength 2*
str(myOSOA)  ## structure for comparison
#>  'SOA' num [1:27, 1:4] 0 13 26 25 2 12 14 24 1 10 ...
#>  - attr(*, "type")= chr "OSOA"
#>  - attr(*, "strength")= chr "2*"
#>  - attr(*, "phi_p")= num 0.101
#>  - attr(*, "optimized")= logi FALSE
#>  - attr(*, "call")= language OSOAs_regular(s = 3, k = 3, optimize = FALSE)
Spat <- Spattern(myOSOA, s=3)
dim_wt_tab(Spat)   ## print method prints NAs as .
#>     1 2 3  4 Sum
#> 1   0 0 0  .   0
#> 2   . 0 0 36  36
#> 3   . . 2 18  20
#> 4   . . .  0   0
#> Sum 0 0 2 54  56
print(dim_wt_tab(Spat), na.print=" ")
#>     1 2 3  4 Sum
#> 1   0 0 0      0
#> 2     0 0 36  36
#> 3       2 18  20
#> 4          0   0
#> Sum 0 0 2 54  56
